## Question 2

**Which of these is the strongest password for a new account?**

- A. P@ssw0rd2024!
- B. **fluffy-mountain-sunrise-jazz** ✓
- C. Tr0ub4dor&3
- D. 12345678#Admin

**Explanation:** Long passphrases made of random unrelated words are both easier to remember and harder to crack than short complex passwords. Length beats complexity — four random words give roughly 50+ bits of entropy. The other options follow predictable substitution patterns that modern cracking tools handle easily.

