## Question 3

**You connect to the free Wi-Fi at a coffee shop to check your work email. What's the biggest risk?**

- A. Your battery will drain faster on public Wi-Fi.
- B. **Someone on the same network could intercept your traffic or set up a fake hotspot.** ✓
- C. The coffee shop's router could slow down your connection.
- D. Your phone's location will be tracked by the Wi-Fi provider.

**Explanation:** Open public Wi-Fi has no encryption — anyone nearby can potentially sniff unencrypted traffic or set up an "evil twin" hotspot with the same network name. Use a VPN on public Wi-Fi and always look for HTTPS. Avoid accessing sensitive accounts on open networks when possible.

