## Question 4

**A pop-up on your computer says "Your device is infected! Call this number immediately to speak with Microsoft support." What should you do?**

- A. Call the number — it's better to be safe than sorry.
- B. Click the pop-up to dismiss it, then call Microsoft's official support line.
- C. **Close your browser, run your own antivirus scan, and report it as a scam.** ✓
- D. Restart your computer and install the software the pop-up recommends.

**Explanation:** This is a tech support scam — one of the most common fraud tactics targeting business users. Microsoft, Apple, and other vendors never send unsolicited pop-ups asking you to call a phone number. Force-close your browser (don't click anything in the pop-up), run a reputable antivirus scan, and report the site.

