## Question 5

**Which of the following best describes good Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) practice?**

- A. Using the same strong password on all accounts so you only need to remember one.
- B. Setting a 6-digit PIN as a second factor for every account.
- C. **Using an authenticator app or hardware key as a second factor.** ✓
- D. Enabling MFA only on your banking app since other accounts aren't important.

**Explanation:** MFA adds a second verification layer so a stolen password alone can't access your account. Authenticator apps generate time-based codes that aren't vulnerable to SMS SIM-swapping attacks, and hardware keys (like YubiKey) are the strongest option. MFA should be enabled on every account that supports it — especially email and cloud services.
